story.text: Today was a supremely unproductive day. I blame Saturday's Rose. Too many sulfites create a continual oppression of my mental functioning.
Tomorrow, I must meditate and exercise. Why on earth did I not bring some athletic clothes? I feel trapped in a cage and it is killing me.
Cannot wait to get out of the city and back to Montana - a first for me.
